Rating: 4
A good and simple recipe that can be varied in a number of ways. Roasted red peppers and balsamic are just a great classic combo. I prefer to roast my own peppers, and add some heat with crushed red pepper. Rosemary can also be subsituted or added to with several different herbs.

Rating: 2
I thought the flavors in this were good, but just not strong enough, even though I marinated it for about 5 hours. I think that the ratio of oil to vinegar should be almost reversed. As it was, I cut back on the oil and double the vinegar; it was still way too oily. The acid in the vinegar is what breaks down the tissue fibers in the meat, so more vinegar would have produced a more tender steak. I don't cook much red meat, so perhaps my technique was off; I'll try this again with more vinegar and less oil and see if it helps. It also set off the smoke detector. I did like the red peppers in this dish (I roast my own so they're not soggy) but only once I put vinegar on top of them in the pan and they turned black and crusty. Yum!

